<div id="review_20779925" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/20779925" />
    <a title="Andy" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/764075-andy"><img alt="Andy" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629118026p2/764075.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/20779925?book_show_action=true">Apr 23, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Andy" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Andy" href="/user/show/764075-andy">Andy</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">numb nuts</span></div>

        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/764075-andy?shelf=gay-lesbian">gay-lesbian</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer20779925" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4436609039411207979">Basically every character in each story is so unbearably neurotic you want to slap them in the face with a dead fish. It’s one thing to create these neurotics in the Fifties (a time when there was a reason for said anxiety). Forty years later to have this nutty behavior in every story is merely annoying.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


