<span id="freeTextContainer17545691222866469865">I&apos;ve read all of Selby Jr&apos;s novels, and have to say that I enjoyed them more than I did this collection. Selby&apos;s work can be hard hitting thematically and challenging to read stylistically, and while this approach was effective at times in this collection, at other times it seemed a little forced. Not a book that I&apos;d consider revisiting and I would recommend investing time in his novels rather than this collection should anyone wish to read his work. </span>
  <span id="freeText17545691222866469865" style="display:none">I've read all of Selby Jr's novels, and have to say that I enjoyed them more than I did this collection. Selby's work can be hard hitting thematically and challenging to read stylistically, and while this approach was effective at times in this collection, at other times it seemed a little forced. Not a book that I'd consider revisiting and I would recommend investing time in his novels rather than this collection should anyone wish to read his work. </span>
